# Coding Standards

## File Naming

- `*.constants.ts` - Pure constant values
- `*.registry.ts` - Typed lookup tables with helper functions
- `*.template.ts` - Factory functions for structured outputs
- `*.types.ts` - Shared type definitions
- `*.schema.ts` - Zod validation schemas (co-located with controllers)
- `*.entity.ts` - Domain entities
- `*.service.ts` - Domain/infrastructure services
- `*.policy.ts` - Domain authorization policies
- `*.use-case.ts` - Application layer orchestrators
- `*.repository.interface.ts` - Repository contracts
- `*.middleware.ts` - Express middleware

## Rules

- Strict TypeScript (`noUncheckedIndexedAccess`, `strictNullChecks`, etc.)
- No `any` - use `unknown` and narrow
- Domain layer must NOT import from Express, Prisma, or infrastructure
- Use `createAppError('ERROR_CODE')` for all business errors
- Use `success()`, `paginated()`, `errorResponse()` templates for responses
- Zod body schemas must use `.strict()` to reject unknown fields
- Log using `logger.info/warn/error(LOG_EVENTS.*, context, metadata)`
- All DB mutations must use `prisma.$transaction()` for atomicity

## Testing

- Unit tests mock Prisma with jest.fn()
- Integration tests use supertest against the Express app
- Auth is mocked via `tests/helpers/setup.ts` (consistent keypair)
- Generate test tokens with `getAuthHeaders()` from `tests/helpers/auth.helper.ts`
